state_name.name: state_name
state_name.comment: Full text name of the state

state_fips_code.name: state_fips_code
state_fips_code.comment: Two digit FIPS code that uniquely identifies each state. State names and their corresponding FIPS codes are available as a BigQuery Public Dataset: `bigquery-public-data.census_utility.census_utility.fips_codes_states`

place_fips_code.name: place_fips_code
place_fips_code.comment: Five-digit FIPS code for the given place. Maps to: `bigquery-public-data.census_utility.census_utility.fips_codes_all`

place_id.name: place_id
place_id.comment: Unique idenifier for each place. This is a concatenation of the current state FIPS code and the place FIPS code

place_name.name: place_name
place_name.comment: Full text name of the place

name_lsad.name: name_lsad
name_lsad.comment: Current name and the translated legal/statistical area description for place

lsad_code.name: lsad_code
lsad_code.comment: A two-character code to describe the general characteristics of a geographic area related to its legal or statistical status,governmental status,and in some cases relationship to other geographic entities. For example, an incorporated place may serve as the statistical equivalent of a county. These map to `bigquery-public-data.census_utility.census_fips_class_code`

principal_city_msa.name: principal_city_msa
principal_city_msa.comment: Indicates if a place is the principal city for a metropolitan or micropolitan statistical area. The polygons defining metropolitan and micropolitan statistical areas are available in `bigquery-public-data.geo_us_boundaries.msa`

principal_city_ne.name: principal_city_ne
principal_city_ne.comment: Indicates if a place is the principal city for a Combined New England City and Town Areas (CNECTA). The polygons defining CNECTA boundaries is available from `bigquery-public-data.geo_us_boundaries.us_cnecta`

functional_status.name: functional_status
functional_status.comment: Current functional status code. A full list of possible results can be found: https://www.census.gov/geo/reference/funcstat.html

area_land_meters.name: area_land_meters
area_land_meters.comment: Area of the place that consists of land, in square meters

area_water_meters.name: area_water_meters
area_water_meters.comment: Area of the place that consists of water, in square meters

internal_point_lat.name: internal_point_lat
internal_point_lat.comment: Latitude of the place's internal point, which is the point at or closest to the place's geographic center

internal_point_lon.name: internal_point_lon
internal_point_lon.comment: Longitude of the place's internal point, which is the point at or closest to the place's geographic center

internal_point_geom.name: internal_point_geom
internal_point_geom.comment: Geographic representation of the state's internal point, which is the point at or closest to the state's geographic center

place_geom.name: place_geom
place_geom.comment: Geographical representation of the polygon that defines the perimeter of each place. This column should be used as the GEO column for visualization in BigQuery Geo Viz
